{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox company | name = Transit Wireless, LLC | logo = | type = [[Private company|Private]] [[Subsidiary]] | genre = | foundation = 2005 | founder = | location_city = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]] | location_country = [[United States]] | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = | products = [[Distributed antenna system]] | services = Cellular phone and wireless data | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = BAI Communications | divisions = | subsid = | slogan = | footnotes = | intl = }} [[File:Wi-Fi and mobile phone antenna inside New York City subway.jpg|thumb|An indoor [[Distributed antenna system|DAS]] antenna installed by Transit Wireless inside a [[New York City Subway]] station]]
'''Transit Wireless''' is an [[United States|American]] [[telecommunication]] company founded in 2005, based in [[New York City]]. It specializes in building wireless communication infrastructure using [[distributed antenna system]] networks to provide [[Wi-Fi]] and [[mobile phone|cellular phone]] coverage in the places that are unreachable by traditional cellular phone services such as in the underground portions of the [[New York City Subway]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Company Overview of Transit Wireless, LLC|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=113927682|publisher=Bloomberg BusinessWeek|accessdate=October 13, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Malykhina|first=Elena|title=36 NYC Subway Stations Get Wi-Fi|url=http://www.informationweek.com/government/mobile/36-nyc-subway-stations-get-wi-fi/240153631|accessdate=October 13, 2013|newspaper=InformationWeek|date=April 25, 2013}}</ref> In 2010, the company was injected with financial support from infrastructure company [[BAI Communications]] for its first project with the [[New York City Transit Authority]], which consisted of adding [[Technology of the New York City Subway#Cellular phone and wireless data|wireless access to subway stations]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Bensinger|first=Greg|title=New York City Subway Platforms to Go Wireless in Revived Accord|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/new-york-city-subway-stations-to-get-mobile-phone-service-in-revived-pact.html|accessdate=October 13, 2013|newspaper=Bloomberg|date=July 30, 2010}}</ref> The company is now a subsidiary of BAI Communications.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bennett|first=Brian|title=NYC subway expands wireless service|url=http://www.cnet.com/8301-17918_1-57581373-85/nyc-subway-expands-wireless-service/|accessdate=October 13, 2013|newspaper=CNET|date=April 25, 2013}}</ref>
